The paper is concerned with evaluating different multiagent learning algorithms in ad hoc team problems, which is a common problem in multiagent systems applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.MA (multiagent systems) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the algorithms with respect to performance criteria such as attainment of equilibrium, social welfare, and fairness, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with agents that are continuously adapting their behaviors, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (systems and control) sub-category.
